rdt.plugin-key: kind
rdt.plugin-name: kind
rdt.plugin-subtitle: Lightweight schema engine — one tiddler per type, namespaced
rdt.section: Reference
title: $:/plugins/rimir/kind/doc/reference
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

<$transclude $tiddler="$:/plugins/rimir/doc-template/templates/page">
<$fill $name="body">

!! Type tiddler fields

|!Field |!Required |!Description |
|`kind.type` |Yes |Unique type key. Instances of this type carry `kind.type: <this-value>`. |
|`kind.fields` |Yes |Stringified-JSON array of field definitions. See //Field def schema// below. |
|`kind.caption` |No |Display name shown in dropdowns, validator headings, etc. |
|`kind.icon` |No |Emoji or short text shown alongside the caption |
|`kind.namespaces` |No |Space-separated namespace memberships. Empty = visible only when active namespace is //(all)//. |
|`kind.parent-kinds` |No |Space-separated list of parent type-keys. Non-empty → ''child kind'' — hidden from global creation surfaces (in-tiddler creator's primary pill row, cascade-palette //Create entity// drill). Only creatable via the per-instance cascade-palette ''Create here…'' action on an existing instance of a kind in this list. Instance back-reference uses the standard `parent` field. Multi-valued for shared children (e.g. `journal training-log`). Validator flags instances whose `parent` is missing OR whose parent's `kind.type` isn't in this list. Editable as a free-text field in Type-builder, OR via a type-safe toggle picker in the cascade-palette //Manage kinds// drill (lists every kind except self, toggling commits to this field). |
|`kind.title-formula` |No |TW filter expression evaluated with `<target-tid>` as the source. Result becomes the new instance's title. Omit for manually-titled types. |
|`kind.auto-children` |No |JSON array. Each entry is `{"kind":"<child-type-key>","fields":{"<field>":"<value>",...}}`. When an instance of this type is saved (via any create path — in-tiddler //Creator// button, cascade-palette //+ New X//, ref-spawn from a `+ Create new …` row, or //Create here…//), each listed child instance is materialised with `parent` pre-set to the new parent's title + per-entry `fields` overrides + the child kind's normal field defaults applied. The child's `kind.title-formula` evaluates against the draft so it sees the back-ref. Entries referencing kinds that don't exist are skipped silently. NOT recursive — auto-children of auto-children don't fire automatically. Editable as raw JSON in Type-builder (3-row textarea), OR via a full CRUD drill in the cascade-palette //Manage kinds// drill — drill into ''auto-children (N)'', list of entries with a //+ Add auto-child entry…// picker, drill into an entry to edit per-field overrides (each as its own text-row, DEL removes the override) plus //+ Add field override…// picker filtered to fields not yet overridden, DEL on an entry-row removes the whole entry. No JSON typing required. |
|`kind.stream-fields` |No |Space-separated field keys shown in the stream-river field bar. Empty / missing = bar is invisible for instances of this type. |

!! Instance tiddler fields

|!Field |!Required |!Description |
|`kind.type` |Yes |The type key. Marks the tiddler as an instance. |
|Field keys from `kind.fields` |Per field's `constraints` |Each field's value is stored as a tiddler field with the name `<key>`. Multi-cardinality values are stored as space-separated lists (TW list-field convention). |

!! Field def schema (entries inside `kind.fields` JSON)

|!Property |!Required |!Description |!Applies to `typed` |
|`key` |Yes |Field key. Used as both the field name on instances and the identifier in `kind.stream-fields` / `kind.title-formula`. |all |
|`typed` |Yes |Editor kind. See //typed values// table. |all |
|`caption` |No |Display label. Falls back to `key` if absent. |all |
|`icon` |No |Emoji or short text. |all |
|`constraints` |No |Array of constraint strings. See //Constraints// table. |all (most relevant for editable types) |
|`options` |Required for `enum` |Array of option strings. |`enum` |
|`ref-types` |Optional for `ref` |Array of `kind.type` values whose instances may be referenced. When empty or absent, all kind-instances in the wiki are selectable (the type-builder displays //(any kind)//). |`ref` |
|`cardinality` |No (default `single`) |Either `single` or `multi`. Multi values are space-separated lists. |`enum`, `ref` |
|`formula` |Required for `$calculated` |Filter expression evaluated with `<target-tid>` as source. |`$calculated` |
|`default` |No |Filter expression evaluated against the draft (`<target-tid>`-as-source subfilter). Materialised onto each fresh instance for fields that would otherwise be blank, re-fired on ref/enum changes so dependent defaults populate after their dependencies are set. Examples: `[[planned]]` (static literal); `[<now "YYYY0MM0DD0hh0mm0ss0XXX">]` (current timestamp in TW canonical form — note single angle brackets in filter context, NOT `<<now …>>` which is wikitext-only); `[get[parent]get[caption]]` (reads parent's caption from the draft); `[get[parent]get[caption]] [[at]] [get[planned-at]format:date[DD.MM.YYYY HH:mm]] +[join[ ]]` (composite — chain `+[join[X]]` for multi-item filters; otherwise only the first item is taken). User-typed values always win (the gate is `!has[<field>]`, not equality with the computed default). |text, longtext, number, date, datetime, url, email, phone, enum |
|`clone` |No |Set to `skip` to exclude this field from the ''+ Clone fields from existing'' copy in the cascade-palette creator (e.g. blank-out a journal `text` field on clone). Default = copy. Computed fields (`$title` / `$calculated`) are always excluded regardless. |all (most relevant on body / unique / computed-ish fields) |

!! `typed` values

|!Value |!Editor |!Notes |
|`text` |single-line input |Free-form short string |
|`longtext` |textarea |Free-form long text |
|`number` |numeric input |Stored as string; validate as needed |
|`date` |TW date picker |TW date format |
|`datetime` |TW date picker w/ time |TW datetime format, 24h |
|`url` |Single-line input (`type="url"`) |Format-checked: must start with `http://` or `https://` (when non-blank) |
|`email` |Single-line input (`type="email"`) |Format-checked: `local@domain.tld` shape (when non-blank) |
|`phone` |Single-line input (`type="tel"`) |Format-checked for German numbers (`+49` or `0` prefix, when non-blank) |
|`enum` |`<$select>` or pill toggle |`options` required; honour `cardinality` |
|`ref` |Typeahead (search + dropdown + selected pills) |`ref-types` optional (empty = any kind-instance); honour `cardinality`; display via target tiddler's caption (falls back to title) |
|`$title` |Read-only |Marks the field as the title position; not editable. Title is computed from the type's `kind.title-formula`. |
|`$calculated` |Read-only |Display-only derived field; value computed from the field's `formula` |

!! Constraints

|!String |!Meaning |
|`required` |Field value must not be blank |
|`min:N` |Minimum N characters (text/longtext) or N entries (multi enum/ref) |
|`max:N` |Maximum N characters or entries |
|`unique` |Field value must not equal another instance of the same type's same field |
|`unique:wiki` |Field value must not equal any other tiddler's same field |

All constraints are blocking — they show up in red in the validator and disable the Create button in the creator.

!! Config tiddlers

|!Path |!Purpose |
|`$:/config/rimir/kind/active-namespace` |Active namespace; empty = all |
|`$:/config/rimir/kind/streambar-max-length` |Truncation threshold for the stream-view field bar (default 20) |

!! State tiddlers

|!Path |!Purpose |
|`$:/state/rimir/kind/draft/<type-key>` |Creator's draft for in-progress instance |
|`$:/state/rimir/kind/edit-mode/<target-tid>` |Per-instance toggle between popup and inline edit mode in stream-view |
|`$:/state/rimir/kind/ta/<target-tid>/<field-key>` |Typeahead search-input state for a ref field |
|`$:/state/rimir/kind/creator/selected-type` |Currently-selected type in the creator |
|`$:/state/rimir/kind/type-builder/selected` |Currently-edited type in the type-builder |
|`$:/state/rimir/kind/type-builder/preview-draft` |Live editor preview's target |
|`$:/state/rimir/kind/cascade-draft/<type-key>` |Manage-kinds ''+ Create new instance'' draft (per type) |
|`$:/state/rimir/kind/cascade-preview-draft/<type-key>` |Manage-kinds side-preview form draft (per type — survives drill-in/out) |
|`$:/state/rimir/kind/cascade-spawn-draft/<parent-tid>/<parent-field>/<ref-type-key>` |Draft for a nested ''+ Create new <X>'' spawn from a ref-field picker (per spawn point — survives drill-in/out and supports arbitrary nesting depth) |
|`$:/state/rimir/kind/create-here-draft/<host-tid>/<target-field>/<ref-type-key>` |Draft for the ''Create here…'' per-instance action (parallel to the spawn draft, but the back-ref direction is inverted — host title is pre-set on the NEW instance's `<target-field>` rather than written to the host's field). |
|`$:/state/rimir/kind/__spawn-result` |Transient capture of the just-spawned tiddler title (used by `kind.cascade-spawn-save` to wire into the parent's ref field) |

!! Engine functions (engine.tid)

|!Function |!Returns |
|`kind.types-all()` |All type tiddlers |
|`kind.locate-type(type-key)` |The type tiddler with that key |
|`kind.active-ns()` |Current active namespace string |
|`kind.belongs-to-ns(active-ns)` |Filter predicate; non-empty if `<currentTiddler>` is in scope |
|`kind.namespaces-all()` |Unique sorted list of all namespaces used by any type |
|`kind.field-keys(type-tid)` |Ordered list of field keys |
|`kind.field-typed(type-tid, field-key)` |`typed` value of the field |
|`kind.field-caption(type-tid, field-key)` |Field caption (falls back to key) |
|`kind.constraints(type-tid, field-key)` |All constraint strings |
|`kind.has-constraint(type-tid, field-key, name)` |Non-empty if constraint present |
|`kind.constraint-num(type-tid, field-key, prefix)` |Numeric value of `min:N` / `max:N` |
|`kind.options(type-tid, field-key)` |Enum option strings |
|`kind.ref-types(type-tid, field-key)` |Allowed ref target type keys |
|`kind.ref-candidates(type-tid, field-key)` |All currently-existing target instances. When `ref-types` is empty, falls back to all kind-instances in the wiki (any `kind.type`). |
|`kind.eval-title(type-tid, target-tid)` |Computed title for an instance |
|`kind.is-child-kind(type-tid)` `kind.parent-kinds-of(type-tid)` `kind.parent-kinds-include(type-tid, candidate)` |Child-kind predicates/getters. Non-empty if `kind.parent-kinds` is set. |
|`kind.top-level-types()` `kind.child-kinds-of(parent-key)` |Filtered views of `kind.types-all()` — top-level (no parent-kinds) vs children of a given parent type-key. |
|`kind.has-ref-field-to(type-tid, target-key)` `kind.ref-back-fields-of(type-tid, target-key)` `kind.kinds-with-back-ref-to(target-key)` |"Create here…" discovery — find kinds whose ref-typed fields list the target as a valid `ref-types` member, and the field-keys on those kinds. |
|`kind.create-here-target-kinds(host-key)` `kind.has-create-here-options(host-tid)` |Union of child kinds + ref-back kinds; the cascade-palette ''Create here…'' action's `ca-applies` gates on this. |
|`kind.auto-children-array(type-tid)` `kind.auto-children-indexes(type-tid)` `kind.has-auto-children(type-tid)` |Raw access to the parent kind's `kind.auto-children` JSON array. |
|`kind.auto-child-kind-at(type-tid, idx)` `kind.auto-child-fields-at(type-tid, idx)` `kind.auto-child-field-value-at(type-tid, idx, field-key)` |Walk one entry — get the child kind's type-key, the field-key list, and individual field values that should override the child kind's defaults. |
|`kind.viol-required(...)` `kind.viol-min(...)` `kind.viol-max(...)` `kind.viol-unique(...)` `kind.viol-unique-wiki(...)` `kind.viol-title(...)` `kind.viol-format-url(...)` `kind.viol-format-email(...)` `kind.viol-format-phone(...)` `kind.viol-parent-kind(...)` |Validation predicates (non-empty = violation). `kind.viol-parent-kind` checks that a child kind's instance has a `parent` whose `kind.type` is in the kind's `parent-kinds` list. |
|`kind.any-invalid(type-tid, type-key, target-tid)` |Non-empty if any constraint is violated on any field |
|`kind.shorten`, `kind.display`, `kind.resolve-ref` |Display helpers |

!! Engine procedures (engine.tid)

|!Procedure |!Effect |
|`kind.compute-default(type-tid, field-key, target-tid)` |Evaluates the field's `default` filter against `<target-tid>`-as-source via `subfilter`. Returns the first result (or empty). Used by `apply-defaults-to` / `force-apply-defaults` and available to any other code that wants to preview the computed default. |
|`kind.apply-defaults-to(type-tid, target-tid)` |Stamps `kind.type` + walks all defaultable fields and writes `compute-default` onto `target-tid` for fields currently blank (idempotent — leaves user-set fields alone). Used by every create path before save, AND re-fired from field-input action chains after each ref/enum change so dependent defaults populate. |
|`kind.force-apply-defaults(type-tid, target-tid)` |Like `apply-defaults-to` but unconditional. Used by the //Reset to defaults// flow. |
|`kind.apply-auto-children(parent-tid, type-tid)` |Walks `type-tid.kind.auto-children` and materialises each entry as a new tiddler with `parent: <<parent-tid>>` + per-entry `fields` overrides + the child kind's own field defaults. Called by every create path after `$action-createtiddler` (parent tiddler title captured via `$savetitle`). Entries pointing at non-existent kinds are skipped silently. Not recursive. |

</$fill>
</$transclude>
